  <main>
    <h2>1. General information</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>FDRS edu</strong> is a supporting mobile application intended to help register participants
      for educational events organized by the <strong>Pharmaceutical Society of the Republic of Srpska</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The app is used solely to enter basic participant details and generate a <strong>QR code</strong> that can be used
      for on-site attendance/participant registration at such events.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data entered in the app</h2>
    <p>
      Users voluntarily enter the information needed to create the QR code (for example: name, surname, and/or other
      event-specific identification details as required by the event organizer).
    </p>
    <div class="note">
      <p><strong>Important:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>The entered data is used <strong>only locally on the user's device</strong>.</li>
        <li>The data is <strong>not sent</strong> to the internet.</li>
        <li>The data is <strong>not transmitted</strong> to any servers.</li>
        <li>The data is <strong>not shared</strong> with any third parties.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>3. Processing and storage</h2>
    <p>The app:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>does <strong>not</strong> store data on remote servers,</li>
      <li>does <strong>not</strong> use cloud services,</li>
      <li>does <strong>not</strong> use advertising or analytics SDKs,</li>
      <li>does <strong>not</strong> perform automated profiling or tracking.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Any data you enter remains on your device and is used only for the purpose of generating the QR code.
    </p>

    <h2>4. QR code</h2>
    <p>
      The QR code generated by the app contains only the data that the user entered. The QR code is intended solely for
      faster and more efficient on-site participant registration.
    </p>
    <p>
      The app does not track how the QR code is used after it is displayed, nor does it have visibility into any
      processing performed by third-party scanners or systems used at the event.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Children’s privacy</h2>
    <p>
      The app is not intended for children under the age of 13 and does not knowingly collect or process children’s personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data sharing</h2>
    <p>The app:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>does <strong>not</strong> automatically collect personal data,</li>
      <li>does <strong>not</strong> sell or share data with third parties,</li>
      <li>does <strong>not</strong> use data for marketing, advertising, or analytics purposes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Security</h2>
    <p>
      Since the app does not transmit data over the network, the risk of unauthorized access through transmission is minimized.
      The user is responsible for device security and for how/when the QR code is displayed.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page and the effective date will be updated.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>App name:</strong> FDRS edu</li>
      <li><strong>Organization:</strong> Pharmaceutical Society of the Republic of Srpska</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> <em>[insert official email]</em></li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin-top: 28px; color:#666;">
